<p>Reviewing change driver information</p><p>Understand the information added for a change driver. 
  </p> 
	  
		<ul> 
		   
			 To edit change drivers, you must
				have the right permissions. 
			  
		   
		 
	 </ul> 
	  
		<p>Change driver information can be
		  added to CORDAP, so that it can be linked to work packages and features. Before
		  you being working on a work package that is linked to a change driver, review
		  the change driver details to ensure your information is current. 
		</p> 
		<p> 
		   
			 <p>Using filters in the Work
				Packages tab, you can easily identify work packages linked to a change driver. 
			 </p> 
		   
		</p>  
		 
		   In 
			 My Products, expand the desired product. 
		   
		 
		 
		  Click the desired release. 
		   
		 
		 
		  Click 
			 Change Drivers. 
		   
		  The list of change drivers included in the selected release
			 appears. 
		   
		 
		 
		  Click the change driver's name to view its details. 
		   
		  If you have permissions, you can also edit the details and click 
			 Save. 
		   
		 
	  
	 The change driver
		details are shown. 
	 